**Disconnected scenario (common in REST APIs):**

```csharp
// API receives PUT /products/42 with partial update DTO
public async Task UpdatePriceAsync(int id, decimal newPrice)
{
    // Option 1: Load → modify → save (round-trip, safest)
    var product = await ctx.Products.FindAsync(id);
    product!.Price = newPrice;
    await ctx.SaveChangesAsync();

    // Option 2: Attach + set specific property (no extra read)
    var stub = new Product { Id = id };
    ctx.Attach(stub);
    stub.Price = newPrice;
    // Only Price is Modified, other columns untouched
    await ctx.SaveChangesAsync();

    // Option 3: ctx.Update — marks ALL properties Modified
    // Risk: overwrites DB columns with whatever is in the entity
    // (e.g., null for properties not in the DTO)
}
```

