**Handling concurrency conflicts:**
```csharp
try
{
    await ctx.SaveChangesAsync();
}
catch (DbUpdateConcurrencyException ex)
{
    var entry = ex.Entries.Single();
    var dbValues = await entry.GetDatabaseValuesAsync(); // current DB state

    if (dbValues == null) { /* row was deleted */ }
    else
    {
        // Option 1: Retry with DB values (last writer wins)
        entry.OriginalValues.SetValues(dbValues);
        await ctx.SaveChangesAsync();

        // Option 2: Show conflict to user
        // throw new ConflictException(entry.CurrentValues, dbValues);
    }
}
```

**Senior note:** For APIs, return 409 Conflict with a representation of the current state. Include an ETag or version field in your API response body derived from `RowVersion`, and require clients to send it back on updates (the "If-Match" HTTP header pattern).

